com.sebuilder.interpreter

Interface StepType

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AcceptAlert, AddCookie, AnswerAlert, Assert, ClearSelections, ClickAndHoldElement, ClickElement, DeleteCookie, DismissAlert, DoubleClickElement, DragAndDropToElement, Get, GoBack, GoForward, MouseOverElement, Pause, Print, Refresh, ReleaseElement, SaveScreenshot, SendKeysToElement, SetElementNotSelected, SetElementSelected, SetElementText, SetWindowSize, Store, Store, SubmitElement, SwitchToDefaultContent, SwitchToFrame, SwitchToFrameByIndex, SwitchToWindow, SwitchToWindowByIndex, SwitchToWindowByTitle, Verify, WaitFor

    public interface StepType
    Interface for classes that define how to run a step of a particular type. Implementing classes should be located in com.sebuilder.interpreter.steptype.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean run(TestRun ctx)
      Perform the action this step consists of.

    • Method Detail

      • run

        boolean run(TestRun ctx)
        Perform the action this step consists of.
        Parameters:
        ctx - Current test run.
        Returns:
        Whether the step succeeded. This should be true except for failed verify steps, which should return false. Other failures should throw a RuntimeException.
